The paper discusses Dirichlet process mixture models (DPMM), which are commonly used in machine learning and statistics. The paper proposes a new method for inference in DPMM that combines sampling-based MCMC and variational methods, which are both commonly used in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.ST (Statistics), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.IT (Information Theory).
